Document: StyleBox
Path: godot/classes/class_stylebox.rst
Summary: Base class for all stylebox types used for drawing UI elements.

Inherits: Resource < RefCounted < Object

Inherited by: StyleBoxEmpty, StyleBoxFlat, StyleBoxLine, StyleBoxTexture

Description: StyleBox is an abstract base class for drawing styles of UI elements. A StyleBox defines how a rectangular area should be drawn, including borders, margins, and background colors. It is used by various UI controls to define their appearance.

Properties:

content_margin_bottom (float): The bottom margin for the content. Default: 0.0.
content_margin_left (float): The left margin for the content. Default: 0.0.
content_margin_right (float): The right margin for the content. Default: 0.0.
content_margin_top (float): The top margin for the content. Default: 0.0.

Methods:

Method: get_content_margin(margin: Side) → float
Returns the content margin for the specified side.

Method: get_draw_rect(rect: Rect2) → Rect2
Returns the rectangle that should be used to draw the stylebox, adjusted for margins.

Method: get_minimum_size() → Vector2
Returns the minimum size that this stylebox requires.

Method: get_margin(margin: Side) → float
Returns the margin for the specified side.

Method: draw(canvas_item: RID, rect: Rect2) → void
Draws the stylebox using the provided canvas item and rectangle.

Method: test_mask(point: Vector2, rect: Rect2) → bool
Tests if a point is within the stylebox's drawing area.

Key Rule: StyleBox is an abstract class and cannot be instantiated directly. Use one of its subclasses like StyleBoxFlat or StyleBoxTexture instead.

Key Rule: Content margins define the area inside the stylebox where child controls or text are placed. These margins are automatically respected by container controls.
---CHUNK---
